    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;divination;\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;druid 2, hunter 2, psychic 2, ranger 2, shaman 2;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 minute<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S, DF<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;long (400 ft. + 40 ft./level)<br>\n    \n    \n    <strong>Effect</strong>&nbsp;magical sensor<br>\n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 minute/level (D)<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;none;&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;no<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p><i>Eagle eye</i> creates a magical sensor directly above you. The sensor can appear anywhere above you, to a maximum height equal to the spell's range. You can see from this vantage as if you were actually there, rotating your viewpoint 360 degrees.</p><p>You perceive with your normal visual senses. A caster using <i>eagle eye</i> can easily see for a considerable distance. The spell does not penetrate any solid surface, although it is unaffected by foliage and the like.</p>\n</div>\n",
